HEADWORD: Pittacal
<hw>Pit"ta*cal</hw> <pr>(p⟦icr⟧t"t⟦adot⟧*k⟦acr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>pi`tta</grk>, <grk>pi`ssa</grk>, pitch +
<grk>kalo`s</grk> beautiful: cf. F. <ets>pittacale</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A dark blue substance obtained from wood tar. It
consists of hydrocarbons which when oxidized form the orange-yellow
eupittonic compounds, the salts of which are dark blue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pittance</ent>⟦br⟧
